Change the Color of Text

<h2 style="color:Red">CatPhotoApp <h2>


Cascading Style Sheets

<style> </style>
The style elements provide a way to edit and change the look of selected elements.
<style>
    h2 {
    color: blue;
    }
</style>

This calls out the h2 header to be the colour blue.
The curly brackets are a must otherwise the code won't work.

<h2 class="red-text"> </h2>
CSS class can create multiple style elements


Style Multiple Elements with a CSS Class
<style>
    .red-text {
        color: red;
    }
</style>
The CSS changes only work when there is a fullstop at the start.


