    <p class="red-text">Kitty ipsum dolor sit amet, shed everywhere shed everywhere stretching attack your ankles chase the red dot, hairball run catnip eat the grass sniff.</p>

    <p class="red-text">Purr jump eat the grass rip the couch scratched sunbathe, shed everywhere rip the couch sleep in the sink fluffy fur catnip scratched.</p>

</body>


Make Dead links

Organisning a elemetns in advance before you know where you want them to link can be done by adding # so it looks like <a href=#>cat photos</a>.
It can also be helpful to use when incorporating Jquery into your website.


Turn an Image into a Link

Nest images within an anchor to make them a link.
<a href="#"><img src="https://bit.ly/fcc-running-cats" alt="Three kittens running towards the camera. "></a>


