Add Placeholder Text to a Text Field

placeholder value of input text to "cat photo URL" edit the existing input type.

<input type="text" placeholder="cat photo URL">


Create a Form Element

Can create web forms to submit data to servers can be done using purely html.
Specify an actionon form element.
The form element needs to be told what to do.
<form action="/url-where-you-want-to-submit-form-data"></form>

Need to add submit cat photo as an action to the form.
<form action="/submit-cat-photo"> </form>


Add a Submit Button to a Form

Submit button can be created from a button's action type.
<button type="submit">this button submits the form</button>

Excercise Add a submit button to your form element with type submit and "Submit" as its text.
<button type="submit"> Submit </button>


Use HTML5 to Require a Field

Can create specific form fields which needs to be filled in before the user can submit the information.
make a text input field required
<input type="text" required>
This field does not work in Safari


Create a Set of Radio Buttons

Radio buttons are a type of input.
If they are related they should have the same name attribute.
To pair radio buttons one needs to be indoor and the other outdoor.
<label><input type="radio" name="indoor-outdoor"> Indoor</label>
<label><input type="radio" name="indoor-outdoor"> Outdoor</label>


Create a Set of Checkboxes

Checkboxes are used in forms and are a form of input.
Related checkboxes should have the same name attribute.
They should be nested within own label element.
<label><input type="checkbox" name="personality"> Loving</label>


Check Radio Buttons and Checkboxes by Default

Checked attribute sets the checkbox or radio button to be checked by default.
<input type="radio" name="test-name" checked>
The form code so far:
<form action="/submit-cat-photo">
  <label><input type="radio" name="indoor-outdoor" checked> Indoor</label>
  <label><input type="radio" name="indoor-outdoor"> Outdoor</label>

  <label><input type="checkbox" name="personality" checked> Loving</label>
  <label><input type="checkbox" name="personality"> Lazy</label>

  <label><input type="checkbox" name="personality"> Energetic</label>
  <input type="text" placeholder="cat photo URL" required>
  <button type="submit">Submit</button>
</form>


